CAPE TOWN - Police in KwaZulu-Natal police on Friday called on the public to help officers find a five-year-old girl from Noghongo, outside Port Shepstone, who has been missing since August 29. "Qobhile Cele (5) who resides at Noqhongo in Mehlomnyama, was last seen by her grandmother on August 29, 2019, playing outside her home," the police said in a statement. "She was wearing a red jacket; blue plastic shoes and grey track pants." Anyone with information is asked to contact warrant officer Zorro Cele on 039 695 3000 or 079 347 4392 or to contact Crime Stop on 08600 10111. African News Agency (ANA)